    <title>Vanilla Ice Cream Recipe</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/recipestyle.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Vanilla Ice Cream</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups heavy cream</li>
            <li>1 cup whole milk</li>
            <li>3/4 cup granulated sugar</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
            <li>1 vanilla bean, split and scraped (optional)</li>
            <li>Pinch of salt</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>icecream</li>
            <li>dessert</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine heavy cream, whole milk, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, and the contents of the vanilla bean (if using). Add a pinch of salt. Mix well until the sugar dissolves.</li>
            <li>Chill the mixture in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours or until it is thoroughly chilled.</li>
            <li>Transfer the chilled mixture to an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer's instructions.</li>
            <li>Once churned, transfer the vanilla ice cream to a lidded container and freeze for at least 4 hours or until firm.</li>
            <li>Scoop and enjoy the classic and creamy Vanilla Ice Cream!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
